'''Marwan Attia Fahim Ghallab''' ({{langx|ar| مروان عطية فاهم غلاب رشوان}}; born 1 August 1998) is an Egyptian footballer who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

== Club career ==
He signed with [[Al Ahly SC]] in the middle of the 2022–23 season amid interest from arch-rivals [[Zamalek SC]] on a four-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |last=أخبار |first= |date=2023-01-10 |title=الأهلي المصري يضم مروان عطية من الاتحاد السكندري |trans-title=Al-Ahly of Egypt add Marwan Attia from Al-Ittihad Alexandria |url=https://www.beinsports.com/ar-mena/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B6%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86- |access-date=2023-12-15 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=ar-mena}}</ref><ref>[https://www.alahlyegypt.com/ar/news/article/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B6%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B9%D8%B7%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%B9-%D8%B3%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B5%D9%81-63bdd74d43766]</ref>

== International career ==
He was called up for the first time to the Egyptian national team in August 2022,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filgoal.com/articles/441509|title=مروان عطية لـ في الجول: لم أكن أعرف أمر انضمامي لمنتخب مصر ولكن توقعته|first=هاني|last=العوضي|date=31 August 2022|website=FilGoal.com}}</ref> before making his first appearance on 24 March 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2023/3/24/%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B9%D8%B7%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%AC%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%89-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B1-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85/6126565|title=مروان عطية يسجل المشاركة الدولية الأولى مع منتخب مصر أمام مالاوى|date=24 March 2023|website=اليوم السابع}}</ref>

On 2 December 2025, Attia was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Attia's father died on 13 July 2023, while Attia was in a camp preparing for the Zamalek match.<ref>[https://www.youm7.com/story/2023/7/13/%D9%88%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B9%D8%B7%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%84-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%85%D8%A9/6240115]</ref> He married his fiancée, Salma Saqr, on 25 July 2024, after postponing it from last year due to the death of his father.<ref>[https://www.vetogate.com/5199779]</ref>

